Example 7: Fe vacancies in maghemite (gamma-Fe2O3)
===================================================

Physical system
---------------
Maghemite (gamma-Fe2O3) can be modelled as a spinel structure with 1/9
of the iron sites vacant. This example starts from the P4(3)32 cubic
structure (space group 212, a=8.344 A) as the ordered reference for the
1x1x3 supercell (168 sites: 12 vacant %Fe + 60 Fe + 96 O). SOD enumerates
all inequivalent ways to fill 4 of the 12 vacant sites with Fe, leaving 8
vacancies and giving the gamma-Fe2O3 stoichiometry (64 Fe + 8 vacancies
+ 96 O). 29 inequivalent configurations are found out of C(12,4) = 495
total arrangements.

The GULP force field uses Fe(III)-O(II) Buckingham potentials and the
oxygen shell model from the Catlow library (catlow.lib).

Species convention in this example
-----------------------------------
  %Fe  = vacant iron site (absent from GULP output)  -- target site
  Fe   = occupied iron site                           -- NOT substituted
  O    = oxygen                                       -- NOT substituted

  newsymbol(1) = Fe   => vacancy filled with Fe
  newsymbol(2) = %Fe  => site remains vacant

Files provided
--------------
  INSOD              SOD input (cell, species, substitution parameters)
  SGO                Symmetry operations for P4(3)32 (space group 212)
  supercell.cif      P1 CIF of the 1x1x3 supercell (168 sites)
  template_input.gin GULP template with catlow.lib
  catlow.lib         Lewis-Catlow force-field library
  n04/               Pre-computed output: OUTSOD, ENERGIES, and
                     GULP input/output files for all 29 configurations

How to run
----------
1. Run combsod:   ../../bin/combsod
2. Run genersod:  ../../bin/genersod
3. GULP input files appear in n04/cXX/input.gin

Notes
-----
- The template_input.gin uses the shell model for oxygen via catlow.lib.
  SOD automatically writes both "O2 core" and "O2 shel" lines.
- Vacancy sites are simply absent from the GULP input -- no special
  keyword is needed in GULP.
